title: Harvey Norman buys $34m stake in dairy co
text:
View Photo 

Homewares retailer Harvey Norman has agreed to pay $34 million for a 49.9 per cent stake in northern Victorian dairy company Coomboona. 
Coomboona owns land and farm assets in the Coomboona district of the Goulburn Valley. 
The business includes dairy farm operations along with a pedigree breeding and genetics division. 
Harvey Norman last week said its annual net profit for fiscal 2015 rose 26.6 per cent to $268.1 million, boosted by property revaluations. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Harvey Norman buys $34m stake in dairy co AAP
